{
  "stem": "12904.3",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And-- but I had my aunt, my mother's sister, my uncle, her husband, and their son and daughter, my cousins, who both were married to Christians at the time.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And I got reacquainted with them and then I decided I would like to go to our house, see what has happened in the house with our house.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And it had changed considerably because it had been heavily bombed, that area.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I was standing in front of the house-- and I give the name of the street and so on-- and I got my camera ready to take a picture when a man opened the front door and asked, [GERMAN].",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was are you looking for something?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I answered, yeah, my [GERMAN].",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Yes, my childhood.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I told him I had lived in the house and asked if he had a family.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The man answered that he had a wife and two daughters to which I responded that it had been the same when we lived there, my parents and two daughters.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Then I added, but we had to leave on account of Hitler.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "With that comment the man closed the door.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I did not take any pictures, realizing that I quote, 'could not go home again.' But then when I went again in '89, 22 years later, there were entirely different people, different family living there, a younger couple.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The man was a scientist and the-- the woman told me that-- they opened the door right away.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "My cousin was with me there, Gunter, the man.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And they opened the door, and I had a-- the companion with me, Susanne, a friend of mine, a young friend of mine, because I was allowed to bring a companion.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And she only spoke English, so the woman immediately spoke English.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
